WEBVTT

00:05.135 --> 00:07.746
Maggie, I'm calling
about some of your mail.

00:07.790 --> 00:09.618
You may have a stalker.

00:09.661 --> 00:11.750
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:11.794 --> 00:13.274
My depression...

00:13.317 --> 00:14.797
it's back.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.886
Come here.

00:16.929 --> 00:18.670
Meredith: You are a fraud,
Maggie Bloom.

00:18.714 --> 00:21.499
Because of you,
my son is dead.

00:21.543 --> 00:23.197
Katherine: There was this girl
in my high school.

00:23.240 --> 00:25.286
Greta Strobe.
We were best friends.

00:25.329 --> 00:28.419
When I found out she was gay,
I didn't know what to say.

00:31.335 --> 00:33.120
Does he know
I was in prison?

00:33.163 --> 00:35.513
I'm sorry, but I can't
work here anymore.

00:35.557 --> 00:37.428
I really need
to talk to her face-to-face.

00:37.472 --> 00:39.343
I know I can help her.

00:39.387 --> 00:41.476
If you're so worried that
I'm gonna destroy your car,

00:41.519 --> 00:43.565
you might as well just
drive me there yourself.

00:43.608 --> 00:45.393
I'm in.

00:45.436 --> 00:47.177
♪♪

00:47.221 --> 00:48.526
Alright.

00:51.094 --> 00:53.357
Maggie: You don't even
know how stupid you sound.

00:53.401 --> 00:55.881
Gary: Oh, my God. I-I'm telling
you, it's "Ahh-ba."

00:55.925 --> 00:58.101
And you lost your credibility
when you claimed it was

00:58.145 --> 01:01.104
pronounced David "Bao-ie",
when everyone on the planet

01:01.148 --> 01:02.801
knows it's "Bow-ie."

01:02.845 --> 01:05.195
Okay, which one of us
lived in Oxford?

01:05.239 --> 01:06.936
You, for almost
two weeks.

01:06.979 --> 01:08.329
Trust me.

01:08.372 --> 01:10.157
The first order of business
when you get to England

01:10.200 --> 01:11.723
is they teach you
the correct pronunciation

01:11.767 --> 01:13.856
for Bowie and ABBA.

01:13.899 --> 01:15.771
It's a requirement
when you land at Heathrow.

01:15.814 --> 01:17.512
Don't you mean "Heath-rao"?

01:17.555 --> 01:18.904
Ohh. How do you
sleep at night?

01:18.948 --> 01:21.472
[ Cellphone buzzing ][ Chuckles ]

01:24.040 --> 01:26.390
Oh. It's right here.
Oh. It's your boyfriend.

01:26.434 --> 01:28.697
Oh. Um, I'll call
him back later.

01:28.740 --> 01:30.916
Camden: Maggie?

01:30.960 --> 01:32.353
Hey!

01:32.396 --> 01:34.137
How's it going?

01:34.181 --> 01:35.704
Fine. Just thought
I'd try you while I can

01:35.747 --> 01:37.053
before this press conference.

01:37.097 --> 01:39.664
Who were you
just talking to?

01:39.708 --> 01:42.145
Uh, it's me...Gare.

01:42.189 --> 01:43.799
G-- It's Gary Mendez.

01:43.842 --> 01:45.975
Oh. Hey, man.

01:46.018 --> 01:48.412
Uh, he's driving me
to Albany.

01:48.456 --> 01:51.459
Turns out the -- the car
came with the driver.

01:51.502 --> 01:55.071
Yeah, dude, uh, it's been
a lifelong goal of mine

01:55.115 --> 01:57.160
to -- to visit
all the state capitals.

01:57.204 --> 02:00.642
So, 1 down, 49 to go.

02:00.685 --> 02:02.774
I just really needed
some moral support,

02:02.818 --> 02:06.213
and he's so precious
with his car.

02:06.256 --> 02:08.476
Totally get it.
I'm glad he's there for you.

02:08.519 --> 02:10.434
Makes me feel better knowing
you've got muscle backing you

02:10.478 --> 02:12.436
if your meeting with
this woman goes south.

02:12.480 --> 02:14.264
Okay, Bruce, coming!

02:14.308 --> 02:16.005
Looks like we're starting.
I gotta run.

02:16.048 --> 02:17.180
I love you.

02:17.224 --> 02:18.486
I love you, too.

02:18.529 --> 02:19.965
I meant that for Gary.

02:20.009 --> 02:21.619
[ Chuckles ]Love you more, dude.

02:21.663 --> 02:22.751
[ Chuckles ]

02:25.014 --> 02:27.103
Wow.

02:27.147 --> 02:29.975
Didn't realize you two were
dropping the L-word.

02:30.019 --> 02:32.587
Yeah. Sorry if that
was weird for you.

02:32.630 --> 02:35.285
No. No, no, no.
I'm happy for you.

02:35.329 --> 02:37.157
I'm even happier now

02:37.200 --> 02:39.463
because you have to love
the Bruins as much as I do.

02:41.030 --> 02:43.163
GPS says
we'll be there in an hour.

02:43.206 --> 02:45.295
What time is Mrs. Bates
expecting us?

02:45.339 --> 02:49.256
Uh, she's not.

02:50.431 --> 02:52.215
I...

02:52.259 --> 02:53.999
She doesn't know
we're coming.

02:54.043 --> 02:57.481
♪♪

03:02.921 --> 03:05.707
[ Cellphone ringing ]

03:05.750 --> 03:12.322
♪♪

03:12.366 --> 03:19.199
♪♪

03:19.242 --> 03:20.635
Regina: Babe?

03:20.678 --> 03:22.854
You gonna get up,

03:22.898 --> 03:25.161
or do you want to
sleep some more?

03:25.205 --> 03:27.990
[ Sighs ]
I'm getting up.

03:28.033 --> 03:29.992
Do you want me to make
chocolate chip pancakes?

03:30.035 --> 03:31.863
I'm not hungry.

03:31.907 --> 03:34.779
Then can I show you
some mime skills

03:34.823 --> 03:36.390
Shanice taught me on set?

03:41.786 --> 03:43.005
Not sure I would've
laughed at that

03:43.048 --> 03:44.572
even if I wasn't depressed.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.965
[ Chuckles ] Hey, that killed
with the assistant director.

03:47.009 --> 03:48.576
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

03:48.619 --> 03:50.404
Oh, man.
Dad again?

03:50.447 --> 03:51.622
Uh-huh.
Yeah.

03:51.666 --> 03:52.971
He's like a teenage girl.

03:53.015 --> 03:54.799
He has called me
every day this week.

03:54.843 --> 03:58.325
He wants to fly up from Miami
for a visit.

03:58.368 --> 04:00.196
Well, now that Angie's
filed for divorce,

04:00.240 --> 04:01.850
he needs a distraction.

04:03.112 --> 04:04.461
I'm sorry.

04:04.505 --> 04:06.202
I mean, it'd be nice
if you'd let the nagging voice

04:06.246 --> 04:08.291
of self-doubt in the back of
my head speak for itself,

04:08.335 --> 04:09.814
but you are right.

04:10.902 --> 04:13.296
So, what are your plans
for today?

04:13.340 --> 04:16.865
Well, Katherine hooked me up
with her contact at the DMV,

04:16.908 --> 04:19.868
and I got the address where
Valerie's car is registered.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.609
I'm gonna go give her
her last week's pay,

04:21.652 --> 04:23.741
and then beg for
forgiveness.

04:26.222 --> 04:27.963
Maybe I should just
stay here with you.

04:28.006 --> 04:30.270
No, no, no, no.
Please go.

04:30.313 --> 04:32.141
I don't want to feel guilty
for keeping you trapped

04:32.184 --> 04:34.012
in the house,
and this is not like before.

04:34.056 --> 04:35.362
I'm not thinking about
hurting myself.

04:35.405 --> 04:38.147
Look, look, I'm already
putting on my house shoes.

04:38.190 --> 04:41.629
And I'm gonna call Dr. Heller,

04:41.672 --> 04:43.457
make an appointment.

04:44.632 --> 04:45.850
Okay.

04:51.029 --> 04:52.292
I'll be back in an hour.

04:52.335 --> 04:58.341
♪♪

04:58.385 --> 05:02.258
[ Door opens ]

05:02.302 --> 05:03.738
[ Door closes ]

05:03.781 --> 05:10.135
♪♪

05:10.179 --> 05:16.968
♪♪

05:17.012 --> 05:19.754
Kiana sent me these shells
from the Gulf of Mexico,

05:19.797 --> 05:21.712
so I have to find something
good to put in my letter.

05:21.756 --> 05:24.019
How about glitter?

05:24.062 --> 05:26.500
Glitter's cancelled, Mom.
It's a micro plastic.

05:26.543 --> 05:29.111
It ends up in the fish,
then it ends up in you.

05:29.154 --> 05:31.374
Uh, paper confetti?

05:31.418 --> 05:32.767
Cool!

05:32.810 --> 05:34.377
Why don't I just send
her a picture of me

05:34.421 --> 05:37.337
standing in what used to
be a rainforest?

05:37.380 --> 05:41.341
Okay, what about an origami
heart made from old newspaper?

05:41.384 --> 05:42.516
Nailed it.

05:44.126 --> 05:45.388
Thanks.

05:47.216 --> 05:49.871
If you want, I can make one for
you to give to your boyfriend.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.265
My -- My boyfriend?

05:53.309 --> 05:55.703
You had a date the other day,
didn't you?

05:55.746 --> 05:57.487
You were wearing
your special perfume.

05:57.531 --> 06:00.272
Oh. Um, you got me.

06:00.316 --> 06:05.495
I, um -- I went out
with someone, um...

06:05.539 --> 06:06.757
but they're not
my boyfriend.

06:06.801 --> 06:07.628
Oh.

06:09.194 --> 06:13.503
So, how are you
with all that?

06:13.547 --> 06:15.070
I'm okay with it.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.638
I mean, I want you
to be happy.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.815
Does Dad know?

06:20.858 --> 06:22.947
Not yet.
It was just a first date.

06:22.991 --> 06:26.081
Well, if you like him,
I hope there's a second.

06:26.124 --> 06:27.865
[ Knock on door ]Carter: Uh, hello, let me in.

06:27.909 --> 06:30.259
I have very important things
to discuss.

06:30.607 --> 06:32.043
[ Chuckles ]

06:32.087 --> 06:33.523
Hey, what are
you doing here?

06:33.567 --> 06:36.961
I have a big update
on the Strobe case.

06:38.093 --> 06:40.487
T, why don't you
head upstairs

06:40.530 --> 06:43.794
and get folding while
we talk business?

06:43.838 --> 06:45.970
S'up, Carter?
Looking fly.

06:46.014 --> 06:47.885
Well, thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

06:47.929 --> 06:51.236
Um, the judge approved
a motion for you to,

06:51.280 --> 06:53.630
um, bump up
the court date.

06:53.674 --> 06:56.590
The defense
has no grounds,

06:56.633 --> 06:59.593
and the evidence is,
um...mounting.

07:01.464 --> 07:03.553
Okay, drop the code.
What'd you find on Greta?

07:03.597 --> 07:07.818
Turns out your former BFF
is living the best revenge,

07:07.862 --> 07:11.082
if being basically a celebrity
tattoo artist is revenge,

07:11.126 --> 07:13.215
which it certainly is
in my book.

07:14.999 --> 07:17.219
Katherine: Wow.
She looks so cool.

07:19.264 --> 07:22.398
Except for apparently
how much she hates me.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.226
I'm sure she doesn't
hate you.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.402
She's just ignoring
your DMs because she's busy

07:26.446 --> 07:27.751
being hot
and sought after.

07:27.795 --> 07:31.059
No, I think she might
really hate me.

07:31.102 --> 07:32.930
What happened
with you guys?

07:32.974 --> 07:36.064
We were best friends
all through middle school.

07:36.107 --> 07:39.284
She stayed over at my house
almost every weekend.

07:39.328 --> 07:41.809
One time, I was sick,

07:41.852 --> 07:44.507
and she got up and went
to the doughnut shop

07:44.551 --> 07:46.509
to help my parents out
with the weekend rush,

07:46.553 --> 07:48.032
and then she ate
too many crullers

07:48.076 --> 07:49.773
and then she got
really sick,

07:49.817 --> 07:50.992
and then we spent the rest
of the weekend

07:51.035 --> 07:52.559
watching Miyazaki films.

07:52.602 --> 07:54.604
Well,
I like her already.

07:54.648 --> 07:57.302
And then sophomore year,

07:57.346 --> 08:00.262
she asked me to go to
the homecoming dance.

08:00.305 --> 08:03.004
What did you say?

08:03.047 --> 08:05.223
I said I was waiting for
John Hatcher to ask me,

08:05.267 --> 08:06.877
and I didn't want to just
go with a friend.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.531
Well, that's not so bad.

08:08.575 --> 08:12.535
And then she said, "I'm not
asking you as a friend."

08:12.579 --> 08:14.494
Oh, my God.

08:14.537 --> 08:17.497
This is like "One Tree Hill",
but with gay stuff.

08:17.540 --> 08:21.413
I just laughed it off
like she was joking,

08:21.457 --> 08:26.680
but I knew she wasn't,
and she knew I knew.

08:26.723 --> 08:30.684
Uh, things were just awkward
after that,

08:30.727 --> 08:34.078
and, um,
I kind of avoided her,

08:34.122 --> 08:36.428
and we haven't talked
since graduation.

08:36.472 --> 08:38.561
Mm, well, there's only
one way to find out

08:38.605 --> 08:40.171
if she's still
mad about it.

08:40.215 --> 08:42.913
File an injunction against her
for a fictitious reason

08:42.957 --> 08:45.220
and be like,
"Ha-ha, just kidding"?

08:45.263 --> 08:48.223
[ Chuckles ] Or you could go
to Strobe Lights.

08:48.266 --> 08:50.007
That's the name of
her tattoo parlor.

08:50.051 --> 08:51.661
Act like you're there
as a customer,

08:51.705 --> 08:53.881
and then you'll have
your chance to apologize.

08:53.924 --> 08:55.839
I'm definitely not
getting a tattoo.

08:55.883 --> 08:57.058
You don't have
to get a tat.

08:57.101 --> 08:58.494
You just have to look like

08:58.538 --> 09:00.409
you're thinking about
getting a tat.

09:00.452 --> 09:01.758
But that's a lie.

09:01.802 --> 09:04.718
Oh, my God. Have you even seen
"One Tree Hill"?

09:04.761 --> 09:06.633
If you want to apologize,

09:06.676 --> 09:09.940
contact must be made
by any means necessary.

09:11.333 --> 09:12.552
[ Door closes ]

09:13.161 --> 09:16.120
Rise and shine,
sleepyhead.

09:16.164 --> 09:17.208
What are you
doing here?

09:17.252 --> 09:18.732
I talked to Gina.

09:18.775 --> 09:19.994
She called, and she told me
what was going on.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.909
She shouldn't have, man.
I'm fine.

09:21.952 --> 09:25.303
Really? Because it is 11:30,
and you are still in bed.

09:25.347 --> 09:28.089
Yeah, 'cause I'm working
on the visualization techniques

09:28.132 --> 09:29.351
Dr. Heller taught me.

09:29.394 --> 09:31.222
Right now, I'm lying
on a beach in Maui

09:31.266 --> 09:33.921
sipping on
a fruity umbrella drink.

09:33.964 --> 09:35.923
The cabana boy's about
to bring me a burger.

09:35.966 --> 09:37.185
Maui? Okay.

09:37.228 --> 09:39.622
Come on.

09:39.666 --> 09:41.668
You're going for a ride.

09:41.711 --> 09:43.234
I promised Regina
I'd keep an eye on you,

09:43.278 --> 09:44.888
and I've got
a whole day planned.

09:44.932 --> 09:46.150
I took a risk there.

09:46.194 --> 09:48.022
I've never been so happy
to see pants.

09:48.065 --> 09:50.328
I'm not getting out
of this bed, man.

09:58.902 --> 10:00.077
Fine.

10:00.121 --> 10:05.039
If you're not getting out,
I am coming in.

10:05.082 --> 10:06.431
You want to be big spoon
or little spoon?

10:06.475 --> 10:08.172
Neither.Little spoon it is.

10:08.216 --> 10:10.958
[ Sniffs ] Oh, Rome,
your bald head smells great.

10:11.001 --> 10:13.917
Bro, take your spoon
and fork off. Seriously.

10:13.961 --> 10:15.223
I didn't want to
have to do this,

10:15.266 --> 10:17.051
but I'm about to roll out
the sweet nothings.

10:17.094 --> 10:18.618
[ Whispering gibberish ]Alright. Okay.

10:18.661 --> 10:20.620
Alright.

10:20.663 --> 10:21.838
Aw, man.

10:21.882 --> 10:23.361
I take it you're
not into ASMR?

10:23.405 --> 10:24.624
Dude, you know I hate
that stuff.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.669
Sends chills
up my spine, man.

10:26.713 --> 10:29.019
Well, at least one of us can
still feel chills in his spine.

10:31.587 --> 10:33.067
Fine.
You can text Gina

10:33.110 --> 10:34.677
and tell her you've
got eyes on me.

10:34.721 --> 10:37.158
But let her know
it's a hostage situation.

10:37.201 --> 10:38.333
Let's go have some fun!

10:43.730 --> 10:46.341
[ Sighs ] I know this whole
thing seems crazy,

10:46.384 --> 10:49.213
but I really have no other way
of getting in touch with her.

10:49.257 --> 10:50.519
♪ We've been waiting♪

10:50.562 --> 10:51.781
Well, how did I not know

10:51.825 --> 10:54.349
that you lost a client
to suicide?

10:54.392 --> 10:58.745
♪♪

10:58.788 --> 11:02.574
Because I never
told anyone.

11:02.618 --> 11:05.403
Justin was actually one
of my first clients

11:05.447 --> 11:06.970
in my private practice,

11:07.014 --> 11:10.713
and he was referred to me

11:10.757 --> 11:13.368
to help with his anxiety.

11:13.411 --> 11:15.762
His brother had
cystic fibrosis

11:15.805 --> 11:17.938
and didn't make it
to high school.

11:17.981 --> 11:19.940
♪ Here we are♪

11:19.983 --> 11:22.420
Well, I certainly get
why you wanted to help.

11:22.464 --> 11:24.074
Yeah, and I think I did.

11:24.118 --> 11:25.510
At first.

11:25.554 --> 11:28.078
I loved that.

11:28.122 --> 11:30.907
But when I realized that
Justin was developing

11:30.951 --> 11:34.215
feelings for me, I tried
to talk to him about it.

11:34.258 --> 11:35.738
And he wouldn't.

11:35.782 --> 11:38.959
So, I referred him
to another therapist.

11:39.002 --> 11:42.005
When I heard that
he had taken his life,

11:42.049 --> 11:45.095
I was devastated.

11:45.139 --> 11:46.793
Not long after that,
I moved to Boston.

11:46.836 --> 11:48.620
♪ This is our place♪

11:48.664 --> 11:50.144
Well,
that's why you knew

11:50.187 --> 11:53.887
so much about what John
was going through.

11:53.930 --> 11:58.674
That whole analogy about
JFK Jr. and his plane.

11:58.718 --> 12:01.764
Yeah. Justin lost sight
of the horizon.

12:04.027 --> 12:06.421
But he wasn't your client
when he died.

12:06.464 --> 12:09.772
So, why is his mother
blaming you?

12:09.816 --> 12:11.513
I mean, you saw
the journal entries.

12:11.556 --> 12:15.909
His feelings for me
didn't end with our therapy.

12:15.952 --> 12:19.347
So...what?

12:19.390 --> 12:21.044
You want to go
set the record straight?

12:21.088 --> 12:22.567
No. No.

12:22.611 --> 12:24.613
It's -- That's not what
this is about.

12:24.656 --> 12:26.484
I heard the pain
in her voice.

12:26.528 --> 12:28.878
This woman has lost
two children.

12:28.922 --> 12:31.794
I just hate the idea that she
might not be getting the help

12:31.838 --> 12:34.579
that she so clearly needs
because of mistakes I made.

12:34.623 --> 12:36.407
What mistakes?

12:36.451 --> 12:38.453
What mistake did you make?

12:38.496 --> 12:42.326
I mean, m-mistakes
she thinks I made.

12:42.370 --> 12:45.025
♪♪

12:45.068 --> 12:47.288
Ugh, I love this song!

12:47.331 --> 12:48.680
[ Volume increases ]Oh.

12:49.681 --> 12:51.379
Oh, yeah.

12:57.080 --> 12:59.648
Hi. I'm looking for
Valerie Sandoval.

12:59.691 --> 13:01.824
I'm Valerie.

13:03.086 --> 13:04.653
Oh.

13:04.696 --> 13:05.872
You're looking
for my mom.

13:07.395 --> 13:12.617
Oh. Um, just want to talk
to her about job stuff.

13:12.661 --> 13:13.880
Is she home?

13:13.923 --> 13:15.838
She doesn't live here.

13:15.882 --> 13:17.840
Oh.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.842
Do you have any idea
where she is?

13:19.886 --> 13:23.063
♪♪

13:23.106 --> 13:24.368
I thought you said
we were gonna have fun?

13:24.412 --> 13:26.022
And we are.

13:26.066 --> 13:27.763
Today's actually
a big day for me.

13:27.807 --> 13:30.592
I am seven rides away from
Mov'n Groov'n status.

13:32.463 --> 13:34.030
Come on.

13:34.074 --> 13:35.597
You'll be Goose,
I'll be Maverick.

13:35.640 --> 13:39.383
I handle the road, you handle
music and climate control.

13:39.427 --> 13:42.212
But remember, be polite.
I have a 4.9 rating.

13:42.256 --> 13:44.519
If I get a 5,
they send me a hat.

13:47.087 --> 13:48.436
Hey, there.

13:48.479 --> 13:49.872
Alright. Joey C.?

13:49.916 --> 13:51.047
Joey C.: Yeah.Great.

13:51.091 --> 13:54.311
Let's find out where
we're headed today.

13:54.355 --> 13:55.530
[ Car door closes ]

13:55.573 --> 13:57.880
The airport. Good.

13:57.924 --> 13:59.708
We will have you
there in...

13:59.751 --> 14:00.535
[ Cellphone chimes ]

14:00.578 --> 14:02.276
...52 minutes.

14:02.319 --> 14:04.060
[ Thunder rumbles ]

14:04.104 --> 14:05.583
Hmm.

14:05.627 --> 14:10.850
♪♪

14:10.893 --> 14:12.764
Woman: Hey, Adam.
So good to see you.

14:12.808 --> 14:15.985
♪♪

14:16.029 --> 14:17.726
Hi.

14:17.769 --> 14:19.032
Cool place.

14:19.075 --> 14:23.863
Just, uh, really like
the artwork,

14:23.906 --> 14:27.431
especially
the single needle designs.

14:27.475 --> 14:28.041
Wondering if --

14:28.084 --> 14:29.346
Name?

14:29.390 --> 14:31.958
Oh, uh, Katherine.

14:32.001 --> 14:33.698
But I don't have
an appointment.

14:35.352 --> 14:36.788
You're kidding.

14:36.832 --> 14:38.138
No.

14:38.181 --> 14:41.010
I thought Greta might
be able to squeeze me in,

14:41.054 --> 14:43.143
get some ink.

14:43.186 --> 14:45.014
Some "ink"?

14:45.058 --> 14:46.276
Let's see.

14:46.320 --> 14:49.627
Greta's next opening
is in three weeks.

14:49.671 --> 14:50.890
Do you want to take it?

14:50.933 --> 14:53.718
Oh. Uh, no.
No, that's okay.

14:53.762 --> 14:56.504
Um, I mean,
maybe I might,

14:56.547 --> 14:59.376
but, uh, I just have to check
my schedule and call back.

14:59.420 --> 15:00.943
Great.

15:00.987 --> 15:04.077
♪ Why would I say
what I would want? ♪

15:04.120 --> 15:07.384
♪♪

15:07.428 --> 15:09.778
Okay.

15:09.821 --> 15:10.910
Bye, then.

15:12.433 --> 15:15.479
Uh...

15:15.523 --> 15:16.611
bye.

15:20.920 --> 15:21.746
Katherine?

15:23.705 --> 15:26.664
Uh, hey, yeah. I-It's me.
[ Chuckles ]

15:26.708 --> 15:29.058
I'm here to
make an appointment.

15:29.102 --> 15:30.973
Um,
but you're very busy,

15:31.017 --> 15:32.975
so I'll just
come back another --

15:33.019 --> 15:34.498
No, no.
I-I'm almost done here.

15:34.542 --> 15:36.848
Just hang on a sec.

15:36.892 --> 15:39.112
Hey, Meetra,
can you push the rest

15:39.155 --> 15:41.679
of my appointments
for today?

15:41.723 --> 15:44.595
My good friend Katherine
wants a tattoo.

15:44.639 --> 15:48.208
♪ In the heart

15:48.251 --> 15:51.602
GPS Voice: You have arrived
at your destination.

15:51.646 --> 15:55.824
♪ You could see♪

15:55.867 --> 15:57.130
[ Engine turns off,
music stops ]

15:57.173 --> 16:00.002
[ Sighs ]

16:00.046 --> 16:01.830
You know, you don't
have to do this.

16:03.658 --> 16:05.790
Maybe we just went
for a long drive.

16:05.834 --> 16:07.836
Took a bit of a detour
through Albany

16:07.879 --> 16:09.359
on our way to
Boston Public Market

16:09.403 --> 16:11.057
for Q's Nuts,

16:11.100 --> 16:14.582
which was a missed opportunity
to name it D's Nuts.

16:14.625 --> 16:16.932
My point is, just because
we came all this way

16:16.976 --> 16:19.108
doesn't mean you have to go
through with it.

16:19.152 --> 16:20.980
Yes, I do.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.026
Can I ask you something?

16:24.070 --> 16:25.549
[ Sighs ]

16:25.593 --> 16:28.509
How is this any different
from you telling Sophie

16:28.552 --> 16:31.642
not to go visit the Gregorys
and her doing it anyway?

16:31.686 --> 16:34.036
Because unlike Sophie,

16:34.080 --> 16:37.213
I'm not here to
try to get answers.

16:37.257 --> 16:40.347
I'm here to help Meredith
get the help she needs.

16:42.479 --> 16:43.698
Okay.

16:44.873 --> 16:47.093
What?
What?

16:47.136 --> 16:51.140
You're trying to fix someone
that hasn't asked for it.

16:51.184 --> 16:53.012
And the only reason I know
that's a problem

16:53.055 --> 16:54.665
is because you've been
telling me that

16:54.709 --> 16:56.276
ever since
I've known you.

16:56.319 --> 16:57.929
Okay. You know what?

16:57.973 --> 17:00.715
Two weeks of therapy with
Dr. Jessica does not make you

17:00.758 --> 17:02.760
an expert
in human behavior.

17:04.849 --> 17:06.547
You're right.

17:08.462 --> 17:12.292
I just know that if I could
go back to Peter's doorstep

17:12.335 --> 17:14.076
and stop myself
from going inside,

17:14.120 --> 17:16.078
that is exactly
what I would do.

17:16.122 --> 17:21.518
♪♪

17:21.562 --> 17:24.086
Maggie.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.740
It's me.

17:27.785 --> 17:29.787
What are
we really doing here?

17:29.831 --> 17:35.097
♪♪

17:35.141 --> 17:36.794
We...

17:40.059 --> 17:42.104
I'm here
to say I'm sorry.

17:42.148 --> 17:45.716
♪♪

17:50.156 --> 17:54.203
So, you probably
saw my DMs.

17:54.247 --> 17:56.597
Oh, no. Um, my assistant
runs my socials.

17:56.640 --> 17:58.164
You sent me a message?

17:59.774 --> 18:04.083
Just that I've been considering
getting a tat for a while,

18:04.126 --> 18:05.693
and, uh...

18:05.736 --> 18:07.651
I heard you're one of
the best artists in town.

18:07.695 --> 18:08.913
Hmm.

18:08.957 --> 18:10.698
What kind of
a tattoo do you want?

18:10.741 --> 18:13.092
Oh. Um...

18:13.135 --> 18:18.140
maybe something around Theo,
my son,

18:18.184 --> 18:22.101
or, I don't know...
personal empowerment?

18:22.144 --> 18:25.278
♪ I can't forget, I can't
forget, I can't forget ♪

18:25.321 --> 18:26.801
Okay, I'm lying.

18:26.844 --> 18:28.759
I didn't really come here
to get a tattoo.

18:28.803 --> 18:32.154
I...I came here
to apologize.

18:32.198 --> 18:34.765
♪ You dripping in sugar
and gold ♪

18:34.809 --> 18:36.941
For what?

18:36.985 --> 18:39.118
For that day
on the beach.

18:40.641 --> 18:45.559
For being so weird when
you asked me to homecoming.

18:45.602 --> 18:48.257
♪ Driving me mango

18:48.301 --> 18:51.391
That was a long time ago.
I-I've let it go.

18:51.434 --> 18:53.784
♪ Driving me mango, mango

18:53.828 --> 18:56.439
It mostly just sucked
losing my best friend.

18:58.311 --> 19:00.617
I know.

19:00.661 --> 19:04.578
I can't imagine what
that was like

19:04.621 --> 19:07.624
to finally reveal your truth
to someone you really care about

19:07.668 --> 19:10.497
and have them
just disappear.

19:12.063 --> 19:14.022
I'm so sorry.

19:15.328 --> 19:17.895
♪ Your hands in my hair

19:17.939 --> 19:19.114
♪ Your hands everywhere

19:19.158 --> 19:20.985
You know, I skipped
the homecoming dance,

19:21.029 --> 19:23.510
and I got my first tattoo
that night.

19:24.467 --> 19:27.035
It was a little Totoro.

19:27.078 --> 19:29.255
Shockingly, the college ladies
didn't love that,

19:29.298 --> 19:31.170
so I got it
covered with this.

19:34.347 --> 19:35.696
I guess in some ways,

19:35.739 --> 19:38.351
I have you to thank
for making me what I am.

19:40.657 --> 19:44.748
Well, I don't know
if this will help or hurt,

19:44.792 --> 19:49.927
but I recently realized
why -- why I pushed you away.

19:49.971 --> 19:52.278
Yeah, you didn't want to be
associated with the queer girl.

19:52.321 --> 19:53.192
I g-- I get it.

19:53.235 --> 19:55.106
No.

19:55.150 --> 19:58.893
It's because I had
feelings for you.

19:58.936 --> 20:02.288
I just didn't realize it
at the time.

20:02.331 --> 20:03.811
I think I was too scared.

20:03.854 --> 20:06.248
[ Chuckles ]
Uh-huh. Sure.

20:07.075 --> 20:08.685
Really.

20:08.729 --> 20:12.559
I, um -- I recently got
divorced,

20:12.602 --> 20:17.128
and, um, a lot of stuff
has come up for me,

20:17.172 --> 20:21.437
stuff I think I wasn't ready
to admit back then.

20:21.481 --> 20:22.917
Wow.

20:22.960 --> 20:25.485
♪ Driving me mad,
driving me mango ♪

20:25.528 --> 20:27.878
♪ Driving me mad,
driving me mango ♪

20:27.922 --> 20:29.532
How about this?

20:30.707 --> 20:32.187
You always
loved the water.

20:32.231 --> 20:35.103
Waves are pretty powerful.

20:35.146 --> 20:36.496
Plus, sometimes,
it takes a minute for them

20:36.539 --> 20:38.846
to catch up to themselves.

20:38.889 --> 20:41.370
[ Chuckles ]

20:41.414 --> 20:42.676
[ Door closes ]

20:42.719 --> 20:44.460
Rome: Dude, I can't believe
he got mad at you

20:44.504 --> 20:45.766
for calling him
Al Pacino.

20:45.809 --> 20:47.550
Eddie: [ As Al Pacino ]
"Hoo-ah!"

20:47.594 --> 20:49.465
[ Laughs ]

20:49.509 --> 20:51.075
[ Normal voice ]
There you go. See?

20:51.119 --> 20:54.383
I knew we could put a smile
on your face today.

20:54.427 --> 20:56.342
Ed, I appreciate what
you're doing, man,

20:56.385 --> 20:58.953
but I-I don't need
a babysitter.

20:58.996 --> 21:00.781
I'm pretty sure I've said
the same thing a few times

21:00.824 --> 21:02.783
over the years,
but no matter what,

21:02.826 --> 21:04.524
you're always
looking out for me.

21:04.567 --> 21:07.266
I can't lose that.

21:13.054 --> 21:17.493
There's a difference between
what I'm feeling now --

21:17.537 --> 21:19.060
like I can't
get out of bed --

21:19.103 --> 21:21.802
and what I was feeling
the last time --

21:21.845 --> 21:24.892
like I couldn't
keep going.

21:24.935 --> 21:27.329
Do you know
what triggered it?

21:27.373 --> 21:29.070
I don't know.

21:29.113 --> 21:32.247
I mean, taking my film
on the road was amazing,

21:32.291 --> 21:33.553
seeing how
it affected people,

21:33.596 --> 21:37.818
but afterwards,
there'd be these conversations.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.994
Everyone needed me
to just hear their own stories

21:40.037 --> 21:41.909
of what it was like
being Black in America,

21:41.952 --> 21:44.477
and I think
it just started sinking in.

21:44.520 --> 21:45.956
Carrying that with me,

21:46.000 --> 21:48.785
feeling like there was only
so much I could do to help.

21:48.829 --> 21:51.310
That makes sense.

21:51.353 --> 21:53.964
Add to that...

21:54.008 --> 21:55.531
waking up
every morning alone

21:55.575 --> 21:57.446
with Gina being gone
for so long.

21:57.490 --> 21:59.361
Have you told her that?

21:59.405 --> 22:00.493
No.

22:00.536 --> 22:01.581
I'm not gonna put that
on her, man.

22:01.624 --> 22:03.452
She needs to live
her life.

22:03.496 --> 22:07.413
She needs to hear
what's going on in your head,

22:07.456 --> 22:10.546
because what was going on
in hers was probably way worse.

22:12.113 --> 22:13.854
[ Cellphone chimes ]Ooh!

22:13.897 --> 22:15.246
Buckle up.

22:15.290 --> 22:16.422
Celtics game
just got out.

22:16.465 --> 22:17.988
Oh, no.

22:18.032 --> 22:19.120
[ Chuckles ]Not doing that.

22:19.163 --> 22:20.687
It's okay.

22:20.730 --> 22:22.906
We have someplace else
we need to be anyway.

22:22.950 --> 22:25.256
Small confession.

22:25.300 --> 22:27.171
This wasn't just about
teaching you the intricacies

22:27.215 --> 22:28.434
of my hustle.

22:28.477 --> 22:30.131
It was a stall tactic.

22:33.613 --> 22:37.007
When I got my diagnosis,
my supervisor suggested

22:37.051 --> 22:39.053
that I put my practice
on hold,

22:39.096 --> 22:41.838
but I kept seeing
a few clients.

22:41.882 --> 22:43.449
You weren't gonna let
cancer win.

22:43.492 --> 22:45.929
No, exactly.

22:45.973 --> 22:47.801
And I really thought
that I could help Justin.

22:47.844 --> 22:51.021
He was processing so much grief
over his brother,

22:51.065 --> 22:54.024
and he was confused
about his feelings for me,

22:54.068 --> 22:57.419
and I was trying to address
all of that at our last session.

22:57.463 --> 23:02.424
And I-I-I reached up
to tuck my hair behind my ear,

23:02.468 --> 23:06.472
and...

23:06.515 --> 23:10.998
a huge chunk of it
came out in my hand.

23:11.041 --> 23:13.957
[ Sighs ]

23:14.001 --> 23:16.612
I started treatment
so quickly.

23:16.656 --> 23:21.661
It was the first time that it --
it hit me that I had cancer.

23:21.704 --> 23:24.054
After that,
I just lost it.

23:24.098 --> 23:26.143
I started crying.

23:27.710 --> 23:31.932
And he came over
to hand me a tissue,

23:31.975 --> 23:36.589
and when I looked up
to thank him...

23:36.632 --> 23:41.376
♪♪

23:41.420 --> 23:43.465
Whatever it is,

23:43.509 --> 23:45.380
you can tell me.

23:47.469 --> 23:49.819
He kissed me.

23:51.865 --> 23:54.737
It was happening
before I even realized it,

23:54.781 --> 23:58.306
and I-I pulled away.

23:58.349 --> 24:01.614
But maybe -- maybe I didn't
pull away as soon as I could've,

24:01.657 --> 24:05.661
but in that moment, I think
I really needed the attention.

24:05.705 --> 24:07.097
[ Sniffles ]

24:07.141 --> 24:10.100
I told him that kissing me
was inappropriate,

24:10.144 --> 24:11.754
and that as much
as he was trying to help me,

24:11.798 --> 24:13.713
that our sessions really
needed to be

24:13.756 --> 24:15.671
about me being there
for him.

24:15.715 --> 24:18.021
[ Breathes deeply ]

24:18.065 --> 24:20.720
And then our time was up.
[ Sniffles ]

24:20.763 --> 24:24.332
And, uh, he left.

24:24.375 --> 24:27.248
The next day,

24:27.291 --> 24:30.643
got an e-mail that he was
canceling our next session.

24:32.558 --> 24:38.172
I tried to follow up, but after
that, it was just...silence.

24:38.215 --> 24:40.435
[ Sighs ]

24:40.479 --> 24:43.830
But, Maggie, you didn't ask
for that kiss.

24:43.873 --> 24:45.222
That's not on you.

24:45.266 --> 24:48.312
No, but I should have
reported it to my supervisor.

24:48.356 --> 24:49.618
That is protocol.

24:50.924 --> 24:51.968
I was just too scared.

24:53.230 --> 24:55.494
He would've looked into
the case.

24:55.537 --> 24:58.671
My license
could've been suspended.

25:01.848 --> 25:03.545
And when I found out
he died,

25:03.589 --> 25:06.026
I tried to put
as much distance as I could

25:06.069 --> 25:08.419
between me and Chicago.

25:08.463 --> 25:11.205
But...
[ Sighs ]

25:11.248 --> 25:14.295
It wasn't until
I saw those journal entries

25:14.338 --> 25:16.515
and the drawing
he made of me

25:16.558 --> 25:18.778
that I realized
how obsessed he was.

25:18.821 --> 25:21.563
Meredith wasn't wrong.

25:22.999 --> 25:24.697
I failed him.

25:27.787 --> 25:29.832
[ Sighs ]

25:30.964 --> 25:32.748
[ Sighs ]

25:34.445 --> 25:38.188
As someone once told me...

25:38.232 --> 25:42.802
when I was blaming myself
for Jon's death,

25:42.845 --> 25:45.108
it is never
just one thing.

25:47.981 --> 25:50.374
Justin lost sight
of the horizon.

25:51.811 --> 25:53.726
Yeah, he lost sight
of the horizon.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.469
But I was
the storm cloud.

25:59.775 --> 26:01.603
[ Sighs ]

26:01.647 --> 26:04.171
So, what's your move,
Bloom?

26:04.214 --> 26:05.564
[ Door closes ]

26:05.607 --> 26:07.827
'Cause I'm guessing
that'syour stalker.

26:07.870 --> 26:12.919
♪♪

26:17.401 --> 26:19.273
I don't know.
I don't know what to do.

26:19.316 --> 26:21.101
My head is so scrambled
right now.

26:21.144 --> 26:23.843
Look, if walking over there
and apologizing to that woman

26:23.886 --> 26:25.845
is gonna make you feel better,
then by all means.

26:25.888 --> 26:27.890
[ Sighs ]Don't let me stop you.

26:30.240 --> 26:31.633
No, that's exactly it.

26:31.677 --> 26:33.461
I...

26:33.504 --> 26:36.029
I'm here to ask
for forgiveness,

26:36.072 --> 26:39.249
but that's to make me
feel better.

26:39.293 --> 26:41.730
Maybe...

26:41.774 --> 26:43.950
Maybe she needs to blame me
for this

26:43.993 --> 26:46.561
so that she doesn't
have to blame herself.

26:50.696 --> 26:54.482
Wow, Dr. Jessica
has got nothing on you.

26:54.525 --> 26:55.831
Don't tell her
I said that

26:55.875 --> 26:58.442
in your secret
therapist chatroom,

26:58.486 --> 27:00.706
which I know exists.

27:04.579 --> 27:07.669
So, what do we do?

27:07.713 --> 27:10.324
We go find
some comfort food?

27:10.367 --> 27:12.935
The Albany equivalent
of Q's Nuts?

27:12.979 --> 27:15.851
No.

27:15.895 --> 27:17.418
No, I need to get back
to Boston.

27:17.461 --> 27:18.419
I need to go on the air.

27:22.336 --> 27:25.556
So, this is
the surprise?

27:25.600 --> 27:27.863
The smell of chlorine
and old socks

27:27.907 --> 27:29.691
supposed to treat
depression?

27:29.735 --> 27:31.693
My trainer Russ works here
on Tuesdays.

27:31.737 --> 27:33.869
He said
we could hang out,

27:33.913 --> 27:36.872
but the pool's
only part of it.

27:36.916 --> 27:37.699
Check it out.

27:42.748 --> 27:45.359
It's not the beach on Maui
you were visualizing earlier,

27:45.402 --> 27:46.447
but it's the best
we could do

27:46.490 --> 27:48.841
in the middle of winter
in Boston.

27:48.884 --> 27:51.495
This guy Russ
must really like you.

27:51.539 --> 27:52.714
He does.

27:52.758 --> 27:54.498
But not as much
as Sophie likes you.

27:54.542 --> 27:56.892
She did all of this.

27:56.936 --> 27:59.503
Said she owed you for
helping her when she
was in a bad place.

28:01.636 --> 28:03.856
It's her way
of saying thanks.

28:03.899 --> 28:10.427
♪♪

28:10.471 --> 28:17.173
♪♪

28:17.217 --> 28:19.175
[ Engine shuts off ]

28:19.219 --> 28:23.745
♪♪

28:23.789 --> 28:26.400
[ Sighs ]

28:26.443 --> 28:28.663
You're a pretty hard woman
to track down.

28:30.186 --> 28:32.406
My new landlord
lives on the second floor.

28:32.449 --> 28:34.756
If you want, you can tell him
all about my criminal record

28:34.800 --> 28:36.149
and then he can raise
the rent on me

28:36.192 --> 28:38.760
just 'cause he knows
he can.

28:38.804 --> 28:41.067
Alright, I deserve that.

28:41.110 --> 28:44.592
I messed up in Miami.
I'm sorry.

28:44.635 --> 28:46.115
Apology accepted.

28:46.159 --> 28:48.552
Now you can stop calling
and texting me every day.

28:51.425 --> 28:53.906
Got this for you.

28:53.949 --> 28:55.559
I forced them to do
more vanilla pumps

28:55.603 --> 28:57.736
than anyone's comfortable with,
just how you like it.

29:02.436 --> 29:04.917
This is also for you --
your last paycheck.

29:04.960 --> 29:08.007
You don't have to pay me.
I didn't work.

29:08.050 --> 29:10.313
You didn't work
because of me.

29:10.357 --> 29:11.662
That's for you.

29:16.102 --> 29:18.844
I don't expect you
to actually forgive me,

29:18.887 --> 29:21.411
but...

29:21.455 --> 29:23.936
at least I was honest
with you.

29:23.979 --> 29:27.809
We spent every day together
for six months.

29:27.853 --> 29:29.028
Why didn't you tell me
you have a daughter?

29:30.681 --> 29:32.335
How do you know that?

29:32.379 --> 29:33.815
Because I met her.

29:33.859 --> 29:35.034
[ Gasps ]

29:35.077 --> 29:36.992
I went to your mom's house
to try to find you

29:37.036 --> 29:38.472
so that I could pay you.

29:38.515 --> 29:40.779
Regina, that's like
five steps too far.

29:40.822 --> 29:41.736
You totally crossed
the line.

29:41.780 --> 29:44.434
She looks
so much like you.

29:45.914 --> 29:47.742
[ Voice breaking ]
You really think so?

29:51.354 --> 29:52.834
[ Laughter ]

29:52.878 --> 29:55.619
Wait, do you remember
Nathan Moretty?

29:55.663 --> 29:57.839
Oh, my God,
how could I forget?

29:57.883 --> 30:00.276
He badgered me for months
wanting to take me

30:00.320 --> 30:03.323
on this, like, dream date
to a place he described as,

30:03.366 --> 30:04.628
"A place so amazing

30:04.672 --> 30:07.109
I couldn't possibly imagine
how magical it was."

30:07.153 --> 30:08.328
Oh, no.

30:08.371 --> 30:10.286
It was the wax museum.[ Laughs ]

30:10.330 --> 30:12.854
And then when I finally caved
and we went there,

30:12.898 --> 30:14.508
I think it clicked for him

30:14.551 --> 30:16.858
that we were not going to
end up together

30:16.902 --> 30:19.643
because I would not
stop staring

30:19.687 --> 30:21.210
at the Drew Barrymore
figure.

30:22.516 --> 30:23.647
He was so disappointed.

30:23.691 --> 30:25.998
Wait a minute.

30:26.041 --> 30:27.390
He asked youout
after that.

30:27.434 --> 30:30.393
Twice, but to be fair,

30:30.437 --> 30:34.093
he asked the whole school,
so I guess he just lost track.

30:34.136 --> 30:35.834
Will you stand for me?

30:38.358 --> 30:41.622
Yeah, or he just
really wanted to go out with

30:41.665 --> 30:43.493
the cutest girl
in our class.

30:43.537 --> 30:45.844
Hardly.

30:45.887 --> 30:50.022
♪ Until another day

30:50.065 --> 30:55.070
♪ Oh, I'm seeing stars

30:55.114 --> 30:59.683
♪♪

30:59.727 --> 31:04.993
♪ Years come down

31:05.037 --> 31:07.256
♪ Cut like an arrow

31:07.300 --> 31:09.780
