and bone ♪

31:11.913 --> 31:14.481
♪ I'm dragging behind

31:14.524 --> 31:17.919
♪ Oh, my God

31:17.963 --> 31:19.355
Oh, wow.

31:19.399 --> 31:21.053
♪ Get up, get up

31:21.096 --> 31:22.141
I love it.

31:22.184 --> 31:23.272
[ Chuckles ]

31:23.316 --> 31:25.796
Okay, let's do it.

31:25.840 --> 31:27.711
Ah, sleep on it
for a few days.

31:27.755 --> 31:30.497
I don't need
to sleep on it.

31:30.540 --> 31:32.020
I get a lot of
recently divorced women in here

31:32.064 --> 31:33.935
making impulsive decisions.

31:33.979 --> 31:36.068
That stencil will last
a week.

31:36.111 --> 31:37.939
You owe it to yourself

31:37.983 --> 31:41.856
to see if this whole thing
is just a phase.

31:41.900 --> 31:44.946
Well, too bad for them,
but this is not just a phase.

31:46.252 --> 31:47.514
I want it.

31:49.777 --> 31:51.953
Now.

31:51.997 --> 31:55.565
♪ Oh, oh

31:57.872 --> 32:00.222
♪ Hey, one more time

32:00.266 --> 32:01.920
♪ Back in the ring

32:04.183 --> 32:05.749
♪ Hey, hey

32:05.793 --> 32:09.188
♪ One more time
back in the ring ♪

32:11.494 --> 32:12.843
♪ Hey, hey

32:12.887 --> 32:16.369
♪ One more time
back in the ring ♪

32:19.850 --> 32:25.334
♪ Ooooh, ooh

32:30.818 --> 32:32.080
Valerie: Vali's dad
was out of the picture

32:32.124 --> 32:35.083
as soon as that pregnancy test
was positive,

32:35.127 --> 32:37.825
but I knew I could manage
raising her alone,

32:37.868 --> 32:40.001
and that's what I did.

32:40.045 --> 32:43.874
Things were good,
but then I got greedy.

32:43.918 --> 32:47.269
Someone taught me how to clone
credit-card numbers.

32:47.313 --> 32:49.445
$10 here, $15 there.

32:49.489 --> 32:50.969
It added up.

32:51.012 --> 32:53.058
I told myself
I was doing it for Vali,

32:53.101 --> 32:57.888
but the truth is
it doesn't really matter why.

32:59.281 --> 33:02.763
I was wrong,
and I got caught.

33:02.806 --> 33:04.895
I was in
for three years.

33:04.939 --> 33:07.463
Three years?
For stolen credit cards?

33:07.507 --> 33:09.988
I was originally sentenced
to two and a half.

33:10.031 --> 33:13.382
I promised Vali I'd be out
for her 13th birthday.

33:13.426 --> 33:16.298
And then my mom said Vali was
getting in trouble at school.

33:16.342 --> 33:18.866
When I heard that,
I got desperate.

33:18.909 --> 33:20.824
I got ahold
of a burner phone

33:20.868 --> 33:22.870
so that I could talk to her
every night.

33:22.913 --> 33:24.219
I mean,
she needed her mom.

33:24.263 --> 33:25.699
Of course she did.

33:25.742 --> 33:29.529
When they found it in my cell,
I got six more months.

33:31.792 --> 33:33.750
I didn't make it out
for her birthday.

33:33.794 --> 33:36.231
And when I finally
did get out,

33:36.275 --> 33:39.278
she made it clear she didn't
want me in her life anymore.

33:39.321 --> 33:42.629
And who could blame her?

33:42.672 --> 33:44.500
I mean,
I'd missed everything.

33:44.544 --> 33:47.677
Her first dance,
her first kiss.

33:48.722 --> 33:50.637
How do you get that back?

33:52.769 --> 33:54.684
You don't.

33:55.946 --> 34:00.690
But as someone
who has pushed away a parent,

34:00.734 --> 34:03.954
I feel confident saying that
you should do whatever you can

34:03.998 --> 34:05.391
to make sure
you don't lose any more.

34:06.870 --> 34:08.133
It's too far gone.

34:08.176 --> 34:10.309
Besides, I could never
give her the life

34:10.352 --> 34:11.310
my parents are giving her.

34:11.353 --> 34:13.355
I can't even get a job
right now.

34:15.836 --> 34:17.359
For a minute in Miami,

34:17.403 --> 34:21.276
I thought I was doing something
that might make Vali proud.

34:21.320 --> 34:24.714
But instead,
I screwed that up, too.

34:24.758 --> 34:26.151
Mnh-mnh,
you didn't screw it up.

34:26.194 --> 34:27.500
I did.

34:27.543 --> 34:32.766
♪♪

34:32.809 --> 34:35.029
I'm sorry
I iced you out.

34:35.073 --> 34:36.900
Hey, it's okay.

34:39.033 --> 34:42.210
I just -- I appreciate
you giving me a second chance.

34:42.254 --> 34:44.212
We all deserve them,
right?

34:46.214 --> 34:48.042
[ Sighs ]

34:49.783 --> 34:52.612
[ Slurping ]

34:52.655 --> 34:54.570
Thank you
for doing this.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.009
I know
it's not gonna fix anything,

34:59.053 --> 35:00.968
but I just wanted to give you
a good day.

35:07.496 --> 35:09.194
Talk to me, Goose.

35:09.237 --> 35:12.414
Did I tell you they're gonna
air my film on PBS?

35:12.458 --> 35:14.808
[ Chuckling ] Dude!
Congratulations, man!

35:14.851 --> 35:17.202
That's so cool.Yes, it is.

35:17.245 --> 35:19.682
And the depression's
still here.

35:22.816 --> 35:25.166
It's why this time
I'm realizing

35:25.210 --> 35:27.908
it's gonna be like this
my whole life.

35:29.910 --> 35:32.478
It's never gonna go away
forever.

35:34.480 --> 35:36.090
I get that.

35:37.309 --> 35:40.703
But I just think

35:40.747 --> 35:42.052
it's about getting up
every day

35:42.096 --> 35:44.011
and doing
what you have to do,

35:44.054 --> 35:46.056
even if it's harder now.

35:52.889 --> 35:54.413
You are absolutely right,
bro.

35:54.456 --> 35:55.675
What's happening?

35:58.591 --> 35:59.548
What are you doing?

35:59.592 --> 36:00.854
Oh,
we're going swimming.

36:00.897 --> 36:02.508
No, Rome,
I'm serious, man.

36:02.551 --> 36:03.596
I don't know if I can swim
like this, come on.

36:03.639 --> 36:04.945
Well,
you said it yourself.

36:04.988 --> 36:07.469
You got to do
what you got to do,

36:07.513 --> 36:09.471
even if it's harder now.

36:09.515 --> 36:18.654
♪♪

36:18.698 --> 36:27.881
♪♪

36:27.924 --> 36:37.064
♪♪

36:37.107 --> 36:46.247
♪♪

36:46.291 --> 36:55.213
♪♪

36:55.256 --> 36:57.258
[ Laughs ]

36:58.955 --> 37:01.349
How's it feel?

37:01.393 --> 37:03.917
[ Chuckles ]

37:03.960 --> 37:05.745
Feels amazing.

37:05.788 --> 37:07.834
[ Chuckles ]

37:10.315 --> 37:12.142
Oh, my God.

37:16.886 --> 37:18.018
[ Laughs ]

37:18.061 --> 37:19.628
Dude!

37:19.672 --> 37:21.587
I think I'm standing!

37:21.630 --> 37:23.676
[ Chuckles ]

37:25.721 --> 37:28.768
Whoo!
Oh-ho!

37:31.379 --> 37:32.946
Bro!

37:32.989 --> 37:34.643
I forgot how tall
you are.

37:34.687 --> 37:36.166
Even in the chair,
I'm taller than you.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.646
Is that right, huh?

37:37.690 --> 37:38.908
Is that really?[ Laughs ]

37:45.654 --> 37:47.177
Well, that was
quite a journey.

37:47.221 --> 37:50.093
Put some clicks
on the old odometer,

37:50.137 --> 37:52.835
worked through
some complicated stuff.

37:52.879 --> 37:55.273
Finally agreed
that Agnetha Faltskog,

37:55.316 --> 37:58.101
Anni-Frid Lyngstad,
Bjorn Ulvaeus,

37:58.145 --> 38:03.368
and Benny Andersson make up
the supergroup ABBA.

38:03.411 --> 38:06.371
Ah, thank you
for coming with me.

38:06.414 --> 38:09.287
And thank you for telling me
what I needed to hear

38:09.330 --> 38:11.506
and not
what I wanted to hear.

38:14.030 --> 38:19.253
I hope you know that no matter
what happened in the past,

38:19.297 --> 38:20.646
you're a really good
human.

38:21.908 --> 38:23.257
I mean it.

38:25.433 --> 38:26.608
You're the best.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.828
[ News intro music plays]

38:28.871 --> 38:30.917
Sports Announcer: Big sports
news out of Pittsburgh tonight.

38:30.960 --> 38:33.093
Camden Lamoureux
of the Boston Bruins

38:33.136 --> 38:35.008
got off the ice
after the second period

38:35.051 --> 38:37.184
and didn't return
for the third.

38:37.227 --> 38:39.229
Word is
it's an ankle injury.

38:39.273 --> 38:40.970
[ Elevator bell dings ]

38:41.014 --> 38:43.277
Hey, it's me.
I just heard the news.

38:43.321 --> 38:46.019
Are you okay?
Call me back.

38:46.062 --> 38:48.369
Wha-- Hey.
Hey.

38:48.413 --> 38:51.067
Oh, my God, I was just --
wait, is your ankle okay?

38:51.111 --> 38:53.200
Oh.

38:53.243 --> 38:54.419
[ Snaps fingers ]
It's fine.

38:54.462 --> 38:56.159
Don't tell ESPN.

38:56.203 --> 38:59.119
When you texted me that
you were going live on the air,

38:59.162 --> 39:00.425
I wanted to be here
with you.

39:00.468 --> 39:02.122
But, Cam, your game.

39:02.165 --> 39:03.993
Eh, so I miss
the last period.

39:04.037 --> 39:05.517
Those guys need the workout,
trust me.

39:05.560 --> 39:07.432
[ Sighs ]

39:07.475 --> 39:09.303
I'm so glad you're here.

39:10.522 --> 39:13.742
Maggie, I should've gone
to Albany with you.

39:13.786 --> 39:15.483
I want that to be my job
from now on.

39:16.484 --> 39:17.833
Claudia: Maggie.

39:17.877 --> 39:19.531
You're on the air
in five.

39:19.574 --> 39:21.010
When Jane comes to kill me,

39:21.054 --> 39:23.056
I'm gonna tell her you tied me
up with a mic cable.

39:23.099 --> 39:25.580
Cam, come with me.Yeah. Good luck.

39:28.757 --> 39:32.065
♪♪

39:32.108 --> 39:34.937
Welcome to
"In the Room with Dr. Bloom."

39:37.592 --> 39:40.943
Tonight, I want to talk about
holding ourselves accountable

39:40.987 --> 39:42.945
for mistakes
when we make them.

39:44.251 --> 39:46.427
Hey, Dad, it's me.

39:46.471 --> 39:49.474
I was thinking,
you should come up next weekend.

39:49.517 --> 39:52.215
I'd love to catch a game
with you.

39:52.259 --> 39:54.914
Maggie: I also want to
talk about forgiveness

39:54.957 --> 39:58.091
and second chances

39:58.134 --> 40:00.180
and to contemplate
what it means

40:00.223 --> 40:05.098
to learn from
and let go of the past

40:05.141 --> 40:10.016
and find a new path forward,

40:10.059 --> 40:12.453
with all of the lessons
we've learned along the way

40:12.497 --> 40:14.194
as our guide.

40:14.237 --> 40:18.024
Rome: [ Sighs ]
Hey, Dr. Heller.

40:18.067 --> 40:19.068
Rome Howard.

40:19.112 --> 40:20.896
Yeah.

40:20.940 --> 40:22.942
Yeah, I-I wanted to make
an appointment

40:22.985 --> 40:24.813
if you have anything
for tomorrow.

40:26.424 --> 40:28.121
O-Okay.

40:28.164 --> 40:29.209
Great.

40:29.252 --> 40:31.559
Y-Yeah, I'll --
I'll see you then.

40:31.603 --> 40:33.169
[ Phone beeps ]Maggie:
Because those lessons,

40:33.213 --> 40:36.564
while sometimes painful
to experience,

40:36.608 --> 40:39.001
will hopefully make things
a little easier

40:39.045 --> 40:40.742
as we go forward.

40:40.786 --> 40:43.310
You told Eddie about
my depression being back?

40:45.225 --> 40:47.140
Yes, I did.

40:47.183 --> 40:48.750
[ Sighs ]

40:48.794 --> 40:50.317
Thank you.

40:52.232 --> 40:53.842
Come here.

40:55.931 --> 40:59.979
And if things
still seem impossible,

41:00.022 --> 41:02.808
just know that leaning on
your loved ones and friends

41:02.851 --> 41:04.723
can help bridge that gap.

41:08.378 --> 41:11.643
You're my favorite spoon.[ Chuckles ]

41:11.686 --> 41:13.819
You may have heard a caller
the other day,

41:13.862 --> 41:16.604
one that was very angry
at me

41:16.648 --> 41:21.217
because of the loss and pain
that she's feeling.

41:21.261 --> 41:24.307
Meredith, if you are listening,
and I hope you are,

41:24.351 --> 41:26.527
I'm sorry that
you've been through so much,

41:26.571 --> 41:28.964
and I hope that
your anger at me

41:29.008 --> 41:32.054
does not stop you from seeking
the help you deserve.

41:32.098 --> 41:35.057
But please just be gentle
with yourself,

41:35.101 --> 41:36.842
because the weight
you are carrying

41:36.885 --> 41:39.627
would crush
even the strongest of us.

41:41.847 --> 41:44.023
And on a personal note,

41:44.066 --> 41:49.289
I also want to thank someone
I leaned on today,

41:49.332 --> 41:54.250
someone who went to great
lengths to be there for me.

41:54.294 --> 41:56.296
Someone I love.

41:56.339 --> 42:01.823
♪♪

